                <HR/>
                <H1>Otmar's List of HTML tags.</H1>

                This list is intended to help edititing HTML documents.
                It is
                <em>not</em> a comprehensive list (HTML, HEADER, TITLE,
                BODY, IMG, ... are missing), but should suffice for basic HTML layout.
                I'm open for suggestions, so please send your comments to me.
                <P/>
                For more complete docs on HTML check out
                <A HREF="http://www.utoronto.ca/webdocs/HTMLdocs/NewHTML/htmlindex.html"
                    >Ian Graham's pages</A>,
                <A HREF="http://werbach.com/barebones/">Kevin Werbach's Bare Bones Guide to HTML</A> or

                <A HREF="http://www.cnw.com/~drclue/Formula_One.cgi/HTML/HTML.html"
                    >Dr. Clue's searchable guide</A>. Hubert Partl wrote a very nice
                <A HREF="http://www.boku.ac.at:80/htmleinf/">HTML Guide in german</A>.
                <A HREF="http://www.hamline.edu/personal/matjohns"
                    >Matt Johnson</A> has collected a
                <A HREF="
                                                  http://www.hamline.edu/personal/matjohns/webdev/html/html/"
                    >comprehensive list of HTML ressources</A> (
                <A HREF="http://www.hamline.edu/personal/matjohns/webdev/html/"
                    >Frame abuse version</A>).
                <A HREF="http://www.ccn.cs.dal.ca/~af380/Profile.html">Norman De Forest</A>
                wrote a
                <A HREF=" http://www.ccn.cs.dal.ca/~af380/html.html"
                    >similar, but more verbose page</A> like this.
                As a style guide I recommend

                <A HREF="http://www.cs.cmu.edu/~tilt/cgh/">Eric Tilton's pages</A>.


                <H2>HEADINGS</H2>

                <BLOCKQUOTE>
                    <H1>Header 1 </H1>
                    <H2>Header 2 </H2>
                    <H3>Header 3 </H3>
                    <H4>Header 4 </H4>
                    <H5>Header 5 </H5>
                    <H6>Header 6 </H6>
                </BLOCKQUOTE>
                <H2>SEPARATORS</H2>
                <UL>
                    <LI> Paragraph Break:</LI>
                    <LI> Line Break:</LI>
                    <LI> Horizontal Rule:</LI>
                </UL>

                <H2>LISTS </H2>
                <BLOCKQUOTE>

                    <H3>UNNUMBERED </H3>
                    <PRE>
                        UL
                        LI apples
                        LI bananas
                        /UL

                    </PRE>
                    <UL>
                        <LI>apples</LI>
                        <LI>bananas</LI>
                    </UL>


                    <H3>NUMBERED </H3>
                    <PRE>
                        OL<BR/>
                        LI<BR/> oranges
                        LI<BR/> peaches
                        LI<BR/> grapes
                        /OL<BR/>

                    </PRE>
                    <OL>
                        <LI/>oranges
                        <LI/>peaches
                        <LI/>grapes
                    </OL>

                    <H3>DESCRIPTIVE</H3>
                    <PRE>
                        DL<BR/>
                        DT<BR/> THHGTGG
                        DD<BR/> "The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy" was originally a BBC
                        radio series which ....
                        DT<BR/> Netrek
                        DD<BR/> Netrek is a networked multiuser game. It is not a simple
                        shoot-em-up game, but ....
                        /DL<BR/>

                    </PRE>
                    <DL>
                        <DT/> THHGTGG
                        <DD/> "The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy" was originally a BBC
                        radio series which ....
                        <DT/> Netrek
                        <DD/> Netrek is a networked multiuser game. It is not a simple
                        shoot-em-up game, but ....
                    </DL>
                </BLOCKQUOTE>

                <H2>PREFORMATTED TEXT </H2>
                <PRE>
                    PRE<BR/>
                    #####  ######  #    #   #####
                    #    #        #  #      #
                    #    #####     ##       #
                    #    #         ##       #
                    #    #        #  #      #
                    #    ######  #    #     #
                    /PRE<BR/>

                </PRE>
                <PRE>
                    #####  ######  #    #   #####
                    #    #        #  #      #
                    #    #####     ##       #
                    #    #         ##       #
                    #    #        #  #      #
                    #    ######  #    #     #
                </PRE>


                <H2>BLOCK QUOTES </H2>
                <PRE>
                    Here is a quote from P. Erdos:
                    BLOCKQUOTE<BR/>
                    "A mathematician is a device for turning coffee into theorems."
                    /BLOCKQUOTE<BR/>
                </PRE>

